solutionCode.python:
    ```python
def check_powers_of_three(n: int) -> bool:
    while n > 0:
        if n % 3 == 2:
            return False
        n //= 3
    return True
```

    The algorithm uses a simple approach by iteratively dividing the given number `n` by 3 (the base of the powers of three). During the division process, it checks if any of the remainders of division is 2. If it finds a remainder of 2 at any stage, it immediately returns `false` since having a 2 in the base-3 representation of the number indicates that it cannot be represented solely by distinct powers of three.

The time complexity of this algorithm is O(log n), as each iteration reduces the number by a factor of 3.

